items.name: Puniru
items.description:
I was going through my old LoRAs and decided to upload some that I didn't before. First on that list is Puniru from Puniru wa Kawaii Slime. I've not seen the show, but the character is cute, so I made it.

Why doesn't my output look like yours?

  1. Check the negatives in my examples. Do you have those embeds?

  2. I used !ADetailer because it's just a set and forget quality bump.

  3. The images were genned at 512x768 then upscaled 1.5 times using 8x_NMKD-Superscale_150000_G with denoising 0.45. You can find it with a quick Google. Note that this upscaler is non-deterministic from my testing so your images may vary slightly. (Check the bottom of this post for info on the cover image.)

Settings and Training:

Trained on Anything v3
Genned on Anything v4.5
LoRA weight 0.8

What's up with the first image?

Since the upscaler is non-deterministic I could just keep trying until both of the hands were correct or I could do what actually happened and get one image with a good right hand and one with a good left hand. Since the upscaler is mostly consistent you can just layer them then erase a hand to get the proper result.

The prompt for the first image may not come through due to this so here is the positive and seed. The negative was the same in every image.

masterpiece, best_quality, 1girl, solo, puniru \(puniru wa kawaii slime\), puniru wa kawaii slime, gradient hair, bangs, green eyes, double bun, mini hat, long hair, jacket, skirt, simple background,

Seed: 330420430

Where have you been? Are you making LoRAs again?

Busy. Just finished my second degree, so I have time now while I send out job apps. I might make more LoRAs, but at the same time I feel this strange aversion when I look at the backlog from comments. Time will tell I guess. For now though I will be uploading 4-5 style LoRAs and a clothing LoRA. Like this character all are pretty old, but not bad quality wise.

items.name: Mystique (X-Men) Lora
items.description:
This Mystique Lora is based off of her comic appearance instead of her movie one. No scales :( .

Works best at strengths of 0.7 - 1. Activation key is "Mystique" followed by "skull belt, white dress, white gloves, thigh thighs," for her signature comic outfit. Her hair length has not been included in the activation key and can be messed with easily. Her transformation ability is NOT included in the Lora, those images were made manually with inpainting.

Realistic checkpoints will have a harder time generating convincing blue skin and fully yellow eyes/sclera. Therefore, more cartoonish/anime checkpoints will look more accurate to the character.

This Lora was made purely for a fun and self-learning experiences. I DID NOT INTEND and DO NOT give permissions for this LoRA to be used for any commercial/promotional/financial gain uses.

items.description:
Polaris [X-Factor]

Trained on NAI, after also training one set on MALWARE DREAM realizing you just don't train it on super customized models. (Yes, you can ask to test the other version, it's just not up on civit.)

Right now this is considered a "BETA" - as in you are going to see things that any OCD comic book fan would throw a book at us for:

  1. Consistently does her headgear incorrectly, mistake in the data (Yeaaaa when you find some really cool data and realize it's edited movie pics of Wanda not Lorna)

  2. Struggles between outfits because we didn't have consistent data of ANY of her outfits, due to not wanting to spend forever and a day training it (Need to ask more about LORA TRAINING) - With this, experiment how you will on "BODYSUIT" and "LEOTARD" - because they both do different things

  3. Also clothing issue: HER MORE CURRENT "BODYSUIT" outfit is VERY close to her old 90s one. She tends to get EASILY mixed up with Enchantress AND VIPER both - as well as other green haired chicks.

  4. Body types WILL VARY even on the NAI version (which is this one) - We had a wide variety of data, including BBW/Voluptuous cosplayers - and welp, SD BE SD!

  5. Hair TYPES varying from decade to decade, we've tried to limit EYE COLOR and HAIR COLOR issues by absorbing those into the activation tags.

How we're going to rectify this: Do more data study, filter the data. It's clearly not ENTIRELY a tagging issue, though I think on clothing that MIGHT be.

If you use it commercially, be aware that you may be at risk for "COPYRIGHT"/DMCA.

items.description:
I'm releasing this as a beta because people were expecting it but I'm going to update in the future as there's things that need improvement. For some reason NAI struggles to make consistent antennae (I believe it gets confused with the antennae that goes over his head on side views) and that made difficult to keep everything looking right.

I have a kofi if you want to support my work. I also take commissions, so if you are interested on a training, check that out. I also have a Pixiv where I upload pics from testing and tease the things I'm working on! Or visit my wife's DA where she has sexy pics of my LoRAs.

His appearance is piccolo, bald, green skin, pointy ears, black eyes, oni horns, pink patches Yes, I replaced the antennae tag for oni horns in the meantime because they tend to be two, be on the forehead and are symmetric, otherwise it ends up with a lot and the face overall is a mess. They can be inpainted the last time I tried at least, so is better to be missing one than have to remove 4. Also, he can have his manga/super heroyellow patches. The source is mostly old, so I recommend using hires with 0.3-0.5 denoise depending on the model.

Is intended for use in weight 1 but play with the value if you are getting too many antennae or is overfitting too much.

The outfits available are:

  • The classic white cape one: white cape, white turban, purple dougi, purple pants, blue sash

  • The fighting one: purple dougi, purple pants, blue sash

  • The driving episode one: yellow t-shirt, purple sleeves, blue baseball cap, backwards hat, jeans

I might add Orange Piccolo with the hope of it helping the antennae situation or if there's demand.

items.name: Black Sclera - LoHa
items.description:
Please check out my Ko-Fi page if you are interested in supporting me.

LoRA commissions open! -> Fiverr

This is a LoHa LoRA! You need the extension! Why? They do a lot better with multi-concepts.

This is retrained from mild's dataset! He was kind enough to share his dataset.

Trigger words for V1.10:

positive: <lora:blackSclera110:1>(black sclera)

I suggest using adetailer for far away shots... Just remember to call the lora and "black sclera" on it.

You can also try to prompt for an iris color like "blue iris" or "green iris" but theres a high possibility of it not generating the expected color.

Follow the steps in the Model Version notes to reproduce my images.

Sample images generated with a merge of Nothingv2.3 + my Clay Mann Style Lora.

All negative embeds should be easy to find. and Prompts should be included in the sample images! Click the little icon in the bottom right to see it.

It was trained on 46 512x512 images provided by mild, 20 epochs using Animefull-final-pruned for the Training Model.

Danbooru tags generated by Waifu Diffusion 1.4 Tagger.

modelVersions.name: v1.10
modelVersions.description:
Generate using a weight of 0.75-1 like this: <lora:blackSclerav110:1>


How I archived my generations:

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps,512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.5, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

items.name: Remarkable Austrian Watercolor Style
items.description:
Art style adopted from a famous Austrian watercolorist.

General opinion on his work is mixed; it has been criticized as being cold and unfeeling, with many arguing that Adolf had greater talent as an architect, demonstrated by how he addressed architecture in his paintings as compared to other details such as trees or people. His style was very calculated when representing architecture in his paintings. Instead of progressing in his artistic influence, his works copied the artists of the nineteenth century and other masters. He claimed to be the founder of many artistic movements but drew primarily from Greco Roman classicism, the Italian Renaissance, and Neoclassicism. He liked the technical ability of these artists, as well as the comprehensible symbolism. [Source]

items.name: Oltopia
items.description:
How to use

It is recommended to write the following tokens: object in the center, sunset, rust, hyper detailed, intricate details, robot, skratches, apocalypse.

Copy the prompt and parameters from the preview to this model â€” you will not lose.

What the model is suitable for

the model is trained on images of aged mechanisms and buildings, as well as on photographs of abandoned buildings and cities.

LoRA was trained on a variety of examples, so try combinations and share your creativity in the comments.

I trained LoRA on the Reliberate model, so it's better to work with her in pairs.

Generation at high resolutions is possible.

Which model works best with

It is best to use the Reliberate model, but you can combine this LoRA with other solutions focused on photorealism, model will work perfectly with them.

  • bad hands embedding

  • bad prompt embedding

  • kunaboto lora

Notes

  • I didn't prune any outfit tags to allow for more freedom(topless,thong/no thong) etc so just use the templates in the images

Training settings?

The most important part of training is getting a good dataset!

Training settings can be found by installing the additional networks extension in auto1111

Extensions -> available -> load from -> additional networks

Restart webui

place lora into stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-webui-additional-networks\models\lora

To view the training settings

Go to additional network tab -> choose model -> training paramters
